farmstay
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a farm offering accommodation (either at the homestead or more usually in former shearers' quarters etc), usually breakfast and sometimes other meals, to holidaymakers.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: OED online under homestay; farmstay used in NZ citation.
Pronunciation:
Notes: Jim Cameron noted reference in a detective novel published in England in 1995.
